Pastor Chris Oyakhilome has continued to provide hope and relief to thousands of Christians from around the globe during the ongoing coronavirus pandemic. Pastor Chris Oyakhilome has united millions in prayers to fight the devastation of the coronavirus and provide relief to those in need. The coronavirus global health crisis has upended economies and threatened to tear the social fabric that binds our society. The pandemic has completely disrupted our way of life now and likely for the foreseeable future. But Pastor Chris Oyakhilome urges Christians not to despair their current situation, but to seek guidance and sustenance from our Lord and savior. Pastor Chris is the founder and lead pastor of Christ Embassy, also known as LoveWorld Inc., an evangelical megachurch with a strong presence in Chris’s native Nigeria, South Africa, Canada, the United Kingdom, and the United States. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-802576" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1.jpg" alt="" width="1080" height="720" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1.jpg 1080w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1-1024x683.jpg.webp 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px">The Global Emergency Relief for Pastors and Ministers of the Gospel One of Pastor Chris’s most prominent messages in his sermons is the tenet of providing charity to those in desperate need and circumstance. Beyond his lessons, the influential pastor’s actions offer a true reflection of his teachings. The Global Emergency Relief for Pastors and Ministers of the Gospel is the latest initiative in Pastor Chris’s multitude of charitable efforts. The first of its kind program is dedicated to aiding pastors left destitute by the Covid-19 pandemic. Our spiritual leaders are the ones we turn to in our most desperate times of need, this initiative ensures that their needs to not go unmet or unnoticed during these challenging times. Pastor Chris described the charitable effort as a meaningful way to contribute as faithful partners by reaching out to the needy. The Christ Embassy network of volunteers has answered Pastor Chris’s call, coming together to ensure the success of the relief effort. Since its launch, the program has provided aid to over 6,000 pastors and ministers in dire need in 50 locations in 16 countries around the world. This is in addition to the 300,000 families and households across the globe impacted by relief programs supported by the Chris Oyakhilome Foundation International. The Global Emergency Relief is just one aspect of Pastor Chris’s efforts https://cofi.online/global-emergency-relief-continues-for-pastors-and-ministers/ to unite Christians worldwide during the coronavirus pandemic. Throughout this difficult time, he has concentrated his efforts on providing for the spiritual needs of all believers, whatever their situation. Pastor Chris Oyakhilome’s Global Emergency Relief Aid has impacted thousands worldwide <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-802576" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1.jpg" alt="" width="1080" height="720" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1.jpg 1080w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/image1-1024x683.jpg.webp 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px">Leading the LoveWorld Nation in Communal Prayer At the annual June Global Communion Service held on June 7th, Pastor Chris declared June as the ‘Month of Prayer’ https://christembassy.org/year-long-prayer-takes-higher-dimension-in-june-the-month-of-prayer/. This declaration holds special meaning as it marks the anniversary of the inauguration of the Pastor Chris Global Prayer Network, which launched several years ago igniting a decade of fervent prayers by partners from all around the world. The Month of Prayer is part of the ongoing theme in what Pastor Chris has declared the year of perfection, consisting of a year-long, non-stop global prayer chain led by Pastor Chris which commenced January 6th, 2020, and will continue until January 6th, 2021. Testimonials from participants in the extended prayer-a-thon have demonstrated the power of prayer’s tremendous impact on throughout the world. In his unique teachings of the Bible, Pastor Chris has often cited prayers as a foundational pillar of faith, a vital communication pathway between Christians and God. Prayer offers hope and sustains the soul in times of uncertainty, such as those that lie before us. The Man of God hosted a Global Prayer service on March 27th that brought together millions of people in a day of prayer against the spread of the novel coronavirus. Pastor Chris was joined by Pastor Benny Hinn in the widely televised event and together the evangelical leaders guided participants in prayer. The prayer service was followed by a week of praying and fasting that has been extended as the battle against the coronavirus continues. Pastor Chris has dedicated his daily television program, “Your LoveWorld with Pastor Chris,” to continue the global prayer chain, initiating several phases of enlightening and transformative sermons centered around prayer and service. Pastor Chris announced a second Global prayer service set to take place on June 26th, emphasizing that the event would carry new meaning for participants whose spiritual growth over the last months cannot be understated. Coronavirus pandemic presents unique challenges The coronavirus crisis has challenged the LoveWorld nation in many ways. Pastor Chris’s supporters rallied behind their beloved pastor after he received criticism related to comments he made about a correlation between the spread of the coronavirus and the building of 5G networks. These statements also led to Ofcom, a British media regulator, to require the LoveWorld television station to add a disclaimer to its programming that acknowledges the views diverged from mainstream evidence. Many of those standing in solidarity with Pastor Chris’s declared that his long history of embracing technology overshadowed any of the statements he made. They cited LoveWorld’s achievement of being the first Christian television network to broadcast internationally live 24/7 from Africa; Pastor Chris’s vast social media presence and the launch of KingsChat, a dedicated LoveWorld social networking app; and the Pastor Chris Digital Library, which offers a wide selection of audio and video files featuring Pastor Chris’s teachings and blessings as evidence of his adoption of new technology in amplifying God’s messages. The yearlong pray-a-thon and the global prayer service demonstrate Pastor Chris’s ability to unite millions of people around the world in communal faith. This is made possible through the use of technology in combination with Pastor Chris’s unique, inspirational leadership ability. <img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-ReDx4O9LPQ/hqdefault.jpg" alt="Your LoveWorld with Pastor Chris --  Phase 7 Day 6">